        "content": "<p>What's the chances that some options could get added to the ig publisher to influence the package cache? For example, it would be good if I could specify WHERE the cache (currently $HOME/.fhir) should be stored/retrieved</p>",
        "id": 161366658,
        "sender_full_name": "Sean McIlvenna",
        "timestamp": 1553188578
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>ex:<br>\njava -jar org..igpublisher.jar -pckcache c:\\some\\specific\\directory -ig ig.json</p>",
        "id": 161366707,
        "sender_full_name": "Sean McIlvenna",
        "timestamp": 1553188614
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>also, it would be good to have an option to clear the package cache</p>",
        "id": 161366739,
        "sender_full_name": "Sean McIlvenna",
        "timestamp": 1553188629
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>ex:</p>",
        "id": 161366744,
        "sender_full_name": "Sean McIlvenna",
        "timestamp": 1553188630
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>java -jar org...igpublisher.jar -clearpckcache -ig ig.json</p>",
        "id": 161366766,
        "sender_full_name": "Sean McIlvenna",
        "timestamp": 1553188645
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>why would you want this?</p>",
        "id": 161392573,
        "sender_full_name": "Grahame Grieve",
        "timestamp": 1553199864
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>We ran into an issue where the cache was holding onto an old version of the US Core package (before the URLs changed from core-r4 to core), and started generating build errors. Deleting the cache folder fixed the error.</p>",
        "id": 161462568,
        "sender_full_name": "Rick Geimer",
        "timestamp": 1553271817
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I had the same problem with an old FHIR cache (3.7.0).</p>",
